					<description><![CDATA[Did you know that Chrome-based browsers (including on Android phones) can interact with Bluetooth Low Energy (LE) sensors and devices without any additional software using the Web Bluetooth API? Bundle that with the off-line features enabled by the progressive web apps (PWA) and we get a real application using pure web technologies and standards. Visit [&#8230;] <a href="https://kaspars.net/blog/sensor-pilot-web-bluetooth" class="read-more excerpt-read-more">Read&#160;more&#160;&#8594;</a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>Did you know that Chrome-based browsers (including on Android phones) can interact with Bluetooth Low Energy (LE) sensors and devices without any additional software using the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Bluetooth_API">Web Bluetooth API</a>? Bundle that with the off-line features enabled by the <a href="https://developers.google.com/web/progressive-web-apps">progressive web apps</a> (PWA) and we get a real application using pure web technologies and standards.</p>



<span id="more-7395"></span>



<p>Visit the <a href="https://kasparsd.github.io/sensor-pilot/">Sensor Pilot app →</a></p>



<p>I started playing with the Web Bluetooth API after getting the <a href="https://kaspars.net/go/xiaomi-mijia-clock-bluetooth">Xiaomi Mijia clock</a> that also also measures air temperature and relative humidity:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://kaspars.net/go/xiaomi-mijia-clock-bluetooth"><img loading="lazy" width="1000" height="491" src="https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/xiaomi-mijia-bluetooth-temperature-humidity-sensor.jpg" alt="Xiaomi Mijia clock with temperature and humidity sensor and Bluetooth LE interface" class="wp-image-7399" srcset="https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/xiaomi-mijia-bluetooth-temperature-humidity-sensor.jpg 1000w, https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/xiaomi-mijia-bluetooth-temperature-humidity-sensor-800x393.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></a><figcaption>Xiaomi Mijia clock with temperature and humidity sensor and Bluetooth LE interface.</figcaption></figure>



<p>Turns out that reading sensor values and updating the time is relatively simple as long as you can get your head around the Bluetooth LE communication patterns such as <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/BluetoothRemoteGATTServer">GATT services</a> and <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/BluetoothRemoteGATTCharacteristic">characteristics</a>.</p>



<h2>Screenshots</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="1024" src="https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/sensor-pilot-desktop-pwa-bluetooth-1024x1024.png" alt="Sensor Pilot Progressive Web App for Bluetooth Sensors on Desktop" class="wp-image-7398" srcset="https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/sensor-pilot-desktop-pwa-bluetooth-1024x1024.png 1024w, https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/sensor-pilot-desktop-pwa-bluetooth-800x800.png 800w, https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/sensor-pilot-desktop-pwa-bluetooth-150x150.png 150w, https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/sensor-pilot-desktop-pwa-bluetooth.png 1491w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption>Google Chrome web browser connected to <a href="https://aranet4.com/">Aranet4</a>.</figcaption></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="1024" src="https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/server-pilot-pwa-screenshot-desktop-2x-1024x1024.png" alt="Sensor Pilot Progressive Web App for Bluetooth Sensors as an app" class="wp-image-7397" srcset="https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/server-pilot-pwa-screenshot-desktop-2x-1024x1024.png 1024w, https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/server-pilot-pwa-screenshot-desktop-2x-800x800.png 800w, https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/server-pilot-pwa-screenshot-desktop-2x-150x150.png 150w, https://kaspars.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/server-pilot-pwa-screenshot-desktop-2x.png 1445w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption>Web app view of the progressive web app connected to <a href="https://aranet4.com/">Aranet4</a>.</figcaption></figure>



<p>The app currently works only with the <a href="https://kaspars.net/blog/aranet4-teardown">Aranet4 Home device</a>.</p>
